com.lightysoft.logmx.mgr

Class LogStreamManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.lightysoft.logmx.mgr.LogFileManager
      • com.lightysoft.logmx.mgr.LogStreamManager
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Cloneable

    public abstract class LogStreamManager
extends LogFileManager
    This class describes a LogFileManager that reads logs from a live stream. Such Manager cannot read backward or forward, and, most of the time, cannot read the next data until it's available (blocking read). This typically occurs when reading through a pipe, socket, serial port, ...

    Managers must always extend this abstract class if they are reading logs from a live stream, instead of extending directly LogFileManager.
    Since:
    LogMX v5.2.0, Manager Specification Version 1.2
    Author:
    LightySoft
    See Also:
    ManagerSpecVersion

      • setHasReadTimeout

        public abstract void setHasReadTimeout(boolean pHasReadTimeout)
        Called by LogMX to tell the Manager if next reads shall be blocking calls or not.
        If LogMX expects that LogFileManager.readLine() or LogFileManager.readEntry() shall be blocking until some data is read, then the parameter pHasReadTimeout will be false. Otherwise, the Manager shall use a timeout mechanism (e.g. java.net.Socket.setSoTimeout()) with a timeout value around 100ms.
        Parameters:
        pHasReadTimeout - true if a timeout shall be used when reading underlying resource, or false if next reads shall be blocking.
        Since:
        LogMX v5.2.0, Manager Specification Version 1.2 (see ManagerSpecVersion)
